===Etymology 2===
From {{etyl|enm|en}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term/t|ang|brōc||brook, stream, torrent}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{term/t|gem-pro|*brōkaz||stream}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{term/t|ine-pro|*mrāǵ-||silt, slime}}. Cognate with Dutch {{term|broek||marsh, swamp|lang=nl}}, German {{term|Bruch||marsh|lang=de}}, {{etyl|grc|-}} {{term|βράγος||tr=brágos|shallows|lang=grc}} and {{etyl|sq|-}} {{term|bërrak||swampy soil|lang=sq}}.

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# A body of running [[water]] smaller than a [[river]]; a small [[stream]].
